14 Amend the amendment in section 2 in Sec. 2. by striking out all of subsection 1-A
15 (page 2, lines 22 to 28 in amendment) and inserting the following:
16 '1-A. For the period from July 1, 2026 to June 30, 2027, if the total weight of the
17 residue generated by a solid waste processing facility and disposed of or otherwise placed
18 in a solid waste landfill exceeds the total weight of the solid waste initially generated within
19 the State that was processed by the facility in that 12-month period, such excess residue,
20 not to exceed 12,500 tons in that 12-month period, is deemed to be waste generated within
21 the State within the meaning of Title 38, section 1303-C, subsection 40-A, as long as that
22 excess residue is composed of oversized bulky waste and is disposed of or otherwise placed
23 in a state-owned solid waste landfill;
24 1-B. For any 12-month period ending prior to July 1, 2026, any additional excess
25 residue associated with the processing of the oversized bulky waste amount identified in
26 subsection 1 generated by the solid waste processing facility in that 12-month period and
27 used at a solid waste landfill, not to exceed 75,000 tons in that 12-month period, is deemed
28 to be waste generated within the State within the meaning of Title 38, section 1303-C,
29 subsection 40-A, as long as that additional excess residue is not composed of oversized
30 bulky waste and is used at a state-owned solid waste landfill as daily cover;
31 1-C. For the period from July 1, 2026 to June 30, 2027, any additional excess residue
32 associated with the processing of the oversized bulky waste amount identified in subsection
33 1-A generated by the solid waste processing facility in that 12-month period and used at a
34 solid waste landfill, not to exceed 37,500 tons in that 12-month period, is deemed to be
35 waste generated within the State within the meaning of Title 38, section 1303-C, subsection
36 40-A, as long as that additional excess residue is not composed of oversized bulky waste
37 and is used at a state-owned solid waste landfill as daily cover; and'
